Hey @anhdvu , unfortunately there are many validators in the bittensor ecosystem that weight copy. Meaning that they don't do any real work, and that they mimimic the weights from another popular validator. The `opentensorfoundation` is a very truthful validator, so you can trust that they are always setting weights properly, and thus that their logs on wandb are good. So, the validators that are weight copying are just mirroring what the rest of the validators think about your miner. This is the case for bascially all subnets. I don't know of a single subnet that doesn't have at least one weight-copying validator

1. You tell the vali youre not going to serve, therefore You don’t reply to the job at all, leading to no emission improvements
